title: CE on control and prevention of infectious diseases (with video)
content_text:
p>
          Following is the transcript of remarks by the Chief Executive, Mr C Y 
          Leung, at a media session today (April 10) at the Hospital Authority 
          (HA) Building after inspecting the HA Infectious Disease Centre at 
          Princess Margaret Hospital and the Centre for Health Protection of the 
          Department of Health: Reporter: Mr Leung, in China, the authorities confirm the new cases 
          every day. So what's your assessment on the situation in China, and

every day. So what's your assessment on the situation in China, and 
          also how can you make sure that the new bird flu would not spread ...? Chief Executive: The Central Government and local governments on the 
          Mainland are very supportive of Hong Kong's efforts. We've been 
          communicating fully. As you know, we sent a delegation to Shanghai to 
          exchange views and experiences with professionals in Shanghai, and we 
          also obtained clinical experiences with them. So we keep full contacts

also obtained clinical experiences with them. So we keep full contacts 
          with our counterparts on the Mainland. Reporter: Mr Leung, are you happy with what you've observed so far? Is 
          there any need to improve ...? Chief Executive: We are happy. We are in a high state of preparedness, 
          and I have full confidence in the professionalism of our medical 
          professionals. Thank you. (Please also refer to the

professionals. Thank you. (Please also refer to the Chinese portion of the transcript.) Ends/Wednesday, April 10, 2013
